39735>>>    // Add code to customize your Zoom View based on how it was invoked.
39735>>>    // Use NavigateData to determine the context this view will be used in.
39735>>>    Procedure OnNavigateForward tWebNavigateData NavigateData Integer hoInvokingView Integer hoInvokingObject
39738>>>
39738>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
39738>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
39738>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
39738>>>        Case Begin
39738>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
39740>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
39740>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
39740>>>                Case Break
39741>>>                
39741>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
39744>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
39744>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
39744>>>                // This would be unusual - normally you drill down from a parent to a list (Select view).
39744>>>                Case Break
39745>>>                
39745>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
39748>>>                // If from child, this is a probably a parent Zoom from a Zoom. 
39748>>>                // This is unusual, but it might be used for adding a new child record.
39748>>>                Case Break
39749>>>                
39749>>>            Case Else // must be nfUndefined
39749>>>                // This may be the start of a query or this may be used for some kind of custom operation.
39749>>>                // You may want to check NavigateData.NamedValues.
39749>>>                  
39749>>>        Case End
39749>>>
39749>>>        // Action buttons can be changed dynamically during a Zoom's display lifetime.
39749>>>        // It's best to set these buttons in their own procedure so you can change later.
39749>>>        Send SetActionButtons
39750>>>
39750>>>        If (HasRecord(Server(Self))) Begin 
39752>>>            Send SetHeaderCaption    ("Entrenador:"*entrenador.Nombre)
39753>>>            Send SetBreadcrumbCaption entrenador.Nombre
39754>>>        End
39754>>>>
39754>>>        Else Begin 
39755>>>            Send SetHeaderCaption     "Nuevo entrenador"
39756>>>            Send SetBreadcrumbCaption "Nuevo"
39757>>>        End
39757>>>>
39757>>>    End_Procedure
39758>>>
39758>>>End_Object
